{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012mNz3ptiH5sYzzCLrk6hzx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonCreator;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     6→\n     7→import java.time.Instant;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * A value object encapsulating the information sent to Barista and Kitchen\n    11→ */\n    12→public class OrderIn {\n    13→\n    14→    public final String orderId;\n    15→\n    16→    public final String itemId;\n    17→\n    18→    public final Item item;\n    19→\n    20→    public final String name;\n    21→\n    22→    public final Instant timeIn;\n    23→\n    24→    @JsonCreator(mode = JsonCreator.Mode.PROPERTIES)\n    25→    public OrderIn(\n    26→            @JsonProperty(\"orderId\") String orderId,\n    27→            @JsonProperty(\"lineItemId\") String itemId,\n    28→            @JsonProperty(\"item\") Item item,\n    29→            @JsonProperty(\"name\") String name) {\n    30→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    31→        this.itemId = itemId;\n    32→        this.item = item;\n    33→        this.name = name;\n    34→        this.timeIn = Instant.now();\n    35→    }\n    36→\n    37→    @Override\n    38→    public String toString() {\n    39→        return \"OrderTicket{\" +\n    40→                \"orderId='\" + orderId + '\\'' +\n    41→                \", lineItemId='\" + itemId + '\\'' +\n    42→                \", item=\" + item +\n    43→                \", name='\" + name + '\\'' +\n    44→                \", timestamp=\" + timeIn +\n    45→                '}';\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    @Override\n    49→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    50→        if (this == o) return true;\n    51→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    52→\n    53→        OrderIn that = (OrderIn) o;\n    54→\n    55→        if (orderId != null ? !orderId.equals(that.orderId) : that.orderId != null) return false;\n    56→        if (itemId != null ? !itemId.equals(that.itemId) : that.itemId != null) return false;\n    57→        if (item != that.item) return false;\n    58→        if (name != null ? !name.equals(that.name) : that.name != null) return false;\n    59→        return timeIn != null ? timeIn.equals(that.timeIn) : that.timeIn == null;\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    @Override\n    63→    public int hashCode() {\n    64→        int result = orderId != null ? orderId.hashCode() : 0;\n    65→        result = 31 * result + (itemId != null ? itemId.hashCode() : 0);\n    66→        result = 31 * result + (item != null ? item.hashCode() : 0);\n    67→        result = 31 * result + (name != null ? name.hashCode() : 0);\n    68→        result = 31 * result + (timeIn != null ? timeIn.hashCode() : 0);\n    69→        return result;\n    70→    }\n    71→}\n    72→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"70712d1b-90aa-4813-9aef-873c0f736b02"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Evnoyia1PSG8cjDQEjKuob","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonCreator;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     6→\n     7→import java.time.Instant;\n     8→\n     9→public class OrderUp extends OrderIn{\n    10→\n    11→    public final String madeBy;\n    12→\n    13→    public final Instant timeUp;\n    14→\n    15→    @JsonCreator(mode = JsonCreator.Mode.PROPERTIES)\n    16→    public OrderUp(\n    17→            @JsonProperty(\"orderId\") String orderId,\n    18→            @JsonProperty(\"lineItemId\") String lineItemId,\n    19→            @JsonProperty(\"item\") Item item,\n    20→            @JsonProperty(\"name\") String name,\n    21→            @JsonProperty(\"timestamp\") Instant timeUp,\n    22→            @JsonProperty(\"madeBy\") String madeBy) {\n    23→        super(orderId, lineItemId, item, name);\n    24→        this.timeUp = timeUp;\n    25→        this.madeBy = madeBy;\n    26→    }\n    27→\n    28→    @Override\n    29→    public String toString() {\n    30→        return \"OrderUp{\" +\n    31→                \"orderId='\" + orderId + '\\'' +\n    32→                \", lineItemId='\" + itemId + '\\'' +\n    33→                \", item=\" + item +\n    34→                \", name='\" + name + '\\'' +\n    35→                \", timestamp=\" + timeUp +\n    36→                \", madeBy='\" + madeBy + '\\'' +\n    37→                '}';\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    @Override\n    41→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    42→\n    43→        if (this == o) return true;\n    44→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    45→        if (!super.equals(o)) return false;\n    46→\n    47→        OrderUp orderUp = (OrderUp) o;\n    48→\n    49→        return madeBy != null ? madeBy.equals(orderUp.madeBy) : orderUp.madeBy == null;\n    50→    }\n    51→\n    52→    @Override\n    53→    public int hashCode() {\n    54→        int result = super.hashCode();\n    55→        result = 31 * result + (madeBy != null ? madeBy.hashCode() : 0);\n    56→        return result;\n    57→    }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"70842b1f-bb66-4f95-a33c-d38f4a2bbebd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WNJsYNxmqR7iFv88n3yEkJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.OrderStatus;\n     5→\n     6→public class OrderUpdate {\n     7→\n     8→    public final String orderId;\n     9→\n    10→    public final String itemId;\n    11→\n    12→    public final String name;\n    13→\n    14→    public final Item item;\n    15→\n    16→    public final OrderStatus status;\n    17→\n    18→    public final String madeBy;\n    19→\n    20→    public OrderUpdate(final String orderId, final String itemId, final String name, final Item item, final OrderStatus status) {\n    21→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    22→        this.itemId = itemId;\n    23→        this.name = name;\n    24→        this.item = item;\n    25→        this.status = status;\n    26→        this.madeBy = null;\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    public OrderUpdate(final String orderId, final String itemId, final String name, final Item item, final OrderStatus status, final String madeBy) {\n    30→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    31→        this.itemId = itemId;\n    32→        this.name = name;\n    33→        this.item = item;\n    34→        this.status = status;\n    35→        this.madeBy = madeBy;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    @Override\n    39→    public String toString() {\n    40→        final StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(\"OrderUpdate{\");\n    41→        sb.append(\"orderId='\").append(orderId).append('\\'');\n    42→        sb.append(\", itemId='\").append(itemId).append('\\'');\n    43→        sb.append(\", name='\").append(name).append('\\'');\n    44→        sb.append(\", item=\").append(item);\n    45→        sb.append(\", status=\").append(status);\n    46→        sb.append(\", madeBy='\").append(madeBy).append('\\'');\n    47→        sb.append('}');\n    48→        return sb.toString();\n    49→    }\n    50→\n    51→    @Override\n    52→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    53→        if (this == o) return true;\n    54→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    55→\n    56→        OrderUpdate that = (OrderUpdate) o;\n    57→\n    58→        if (orderId != null ? !orderId.equals(that.orderId) : that.orderId != null) return false;\n    59→        if (itemId != null ? !itemId.equals(that.itemId) : that.itemId != null) return false;\n    60→        if (name != null ? !name.equals(that.name) : that.name != null) return false;\n    61→        if (item != that.item) return false;\n    62→        if (status != that.status) return false;\n    63→        return madeBy != null ? madeBy.equals(that.madeBy) : that.madeBy == null;\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    @Override\n    67→    public int hashCode() {\n    68→        int result = orderId != null ? orderId.hashCode() : 0;\n    69→        result = 31 * result + (itemId != null ? itemId.hashCode() : 0);\n    70→        result = 31 * result + (name != null ? name.hashCode() : 0);\n    71→        result = 31 * result + (item != null ? item.hashCode() : 0);\n    72→        result = 31 * result + (status != null ? status.hashCode() : 0);\n    73→        result = 31 * result + (madeBy != null ? madeBy.hashCode() : 0);\n    74→        return result;\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→\n    78→}\n    79→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"c44988db-cbf6-4843-b619-c40c7b4b8c2b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SqoZnzbDuBxpXWK3MmxHEK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.infrastructure;\n     2→\n     3→public class EventBusTopics {\n     4→\n     5→    public static final String WEB_UPDATES = \"web-updates\";\n     6→    public static final String BARISTA_IN = \"barista-in\";\n     7→    public static final String KITCHEN_IN = \"kitchen-in\";\n     8→    public static final String ORDERS_UP = \"orders-up\";\n     9→\n    10→}\n    11→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"6e7070e4-948c-4edc-8349-96e12abe6393"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Gs4vGXXiHToPGd8P6q8XBs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.infrastructure;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheRepository;\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Order;\n     5→\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→\n     8→@ApplicationScoped\n     9→public class OrderRepository implements PanacheRepository<Order> {\n    10→\n    11→    public Order findById(final String id) {\n    12→        return Order.findById(id);\n    13→    }\n    14→}\n    15→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"4cb51bff-5bb5-42df-aee7-2f0341b568cb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RKica9TqH2kBCwoZNuvX6v","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.kitchen;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderIn;\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderUp;\n     5→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.Message;\n     6→\n     7→public interface Kitchen {\n     8→\n     9→    public void onOrderIn(Message message);\n    10→}\n    11→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"ca8f7c85-7898-42df-bd99-0e31f61c8924"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011EqHiTEzs6tnxvowbULfxJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.kitchen;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.vertx.ConsumeEvent;\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderIn;\n     6→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderUp;\n     7→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.kitchen.domain.KitchenOrder;\n     8→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.kitchen.domain.KitchenOrderRepository;\n     9→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.utils.JsonUtil;\n    10→import io.smallrye.common.annotation.Blocking;\n    11→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.EventBus;\n    12→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.Message;\n    13→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n    14→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n    15→\n    16→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    17→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    18→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    19→import java.time.Instant;\n    20→\n    21→import static io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.infrastructure.EventBusTopics.*;\n    22→\n    23→@ApplicationScoped\n    24→public class KitchenImpl implements Kitchen {\n    25→\n    26→    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(KitchenImpl.class);\n    27→\n    28→    String madeBy = \"Sulu\";\n    29→\n    30→    @Inject\n    31→    EventBus eventBus;\n    32→\n    33→    @Inject\n    34→    KitchenOrderRepository kitchenOrderRepository;\n    35→\n    36→    @ConsumeEvent(KITCHEN_IN)\n    37→    @Blocking\n    38→    @Transactional\n    39→    public void onOrderIn(final Message message) {\n    40→        OrderIn orderIn = JsonUtil.fromJson(message.body().toString(), OrderIn.class);\n    41→        KitchenOrder kitchenOrder = new KitchenOrder(orderIn.orderId, orderIn.item, Instant.now());\n    42→        LOGGER.debug(\"order in : {}\", orderIn);\n    43→        try {\n    44→            Thread.sleep(calculateDelay(orderIn.item));\n    45→        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\n    46→            e.printStackTrace();\n    47→        }\n    48→        OrderUp orderUp = new OrderUp(\n    49→                orderIn.orderId,\n    50→                orderIn.itemId,\n    51→                orderIn.item,\n    52→                orderIn.name,\n    53→                Instant.now(),\n    54→                madeBy);\n    55→        kitchenOrder.setTimeUp(Instant.now());\n    56→        kitchenOrderRepository.persist(kitchenOrder);\n    57→        eventBus.<OrderUp>publish(ORDERS_UP, JsonUtil.toJson(orderUp));\n    58→\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    private int calculateDelay(final Item item) {\n    62→        switch (item) {\n    63→            case CROISSANT:\n    64→                return 7000;\n    65→            case CROISSANT_CHOCOLATE:\n    66→                return 7000;\n    67→            case CAKEPOP:\n    68→                return 5000;\n    69→            case MUFFIN:\n    70→                return 7000;\n    71→            default:\n    72→                return 3000;\n    73→        }\n    74→    }\n    75→}\n    76→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"4d9987cb-6436-4910-9113-f9ce6224fd6b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TA72CLzpm3FhN2X391eW1r","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.kitchen.domain;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntity;\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     5→\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.EnumType;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.Enumerated;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    10→import java.time.Instant;\n    11→\n    12→@Entity @Table(name = \"kitchen_order\", schema = \"kitchen\")\n    13→public class KitchenOrder extends PanacheEntity {\n    14→\n    15→    private String orderId;\n    16→\n    17→    @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    18→    private Item item;\n    19→\n    20→    private Instant timeIn;\n    21→\n    22→    private Instant timeUp;\n    23→\n    24→    public KitchenOrder() {\n    25→    }\n    26→\n    27→\n    28→    public KitchenOrder(String orderId, Item item, Instant timeIn) {\n    29→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    30→        this.item = item;\n    31→        this.timeIn = timeIn;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    public KitchenOrder(String orderId, Item item, Instant timeIn, Instant timeUp) {\n    35→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    36→        this.item = item;\n    37→        this.timeIn = timeIn;\n    38→        this.timeUp = timeUp;\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    @Override\n    42→    public String toString() {\n    43→        final StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(\"KitchenOrder{\");\n    44→        sb.append(\"orderId='\").append(orderId).append('\\'');\n    45→        sb.append(\", item=\").append(item);\n    46→        sb.append(\", timeIn=\").append(timeIn);\n    47→        sb.append(\", timeUp=\").append(timeUp);\n    48→        sb.append('}');\n    49→        return sb.toString();\n    50→    }\n    51→\n    52→    @Override\n    53→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    54→        if (this == o) return true;\n    55→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    56→\n    57→        KitchenOrder that = (KitchenOrder) o;\n    58→\n    59→        if (orderId != null ? !orderId.equals(that.orderId) : that.orderId != null) return false;\n    60→        if (item != that.item) return false;\n    61→        if (timeIn != null ? !timeIn.equals(that.timeIn) : that.timeIn != null) return false;\n    62→        return timeUp != null ? timeUp.equals(that.timeUp) : that.timeUp == null;\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→    @Override\n    66→    public int hashCode() {\n    67→        int result = orderId != null ? orderId.hashCode() : 0;\n    68→        result = 31 * result + (item != null ? item.hashCode() : 0);\n    69→        result = 31 * result + (timeIn != null ? timeIn.hashCode() : 0);\n    70→        result = 31 * result + (timeUp != null ? timeUp.hashCode() : 0);\n    71→        return result;\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    public String getOrderId() {\n    75→        return orderId;\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    public void setOrderId(String orderId) {\n    79→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    80→    }\n    81→\n    82→    public Item getItem() {\n    83→        return item;\n    84→    }\n    85→\n    86→    public void setItem(Item item) {\n    87→        this.item = item;\n    88→    }\n    89→\n    90→    public Instant getTimeIn() {\n    91→        return timeIn;\n    92→    }\n    93→\n    94→    public void setTimeIn(Instant timeIn) {\n    95→        this.timeIn = timeIn;\n    96→    }\n    97→\n    98→    public Instant getTimeUp() {\n    99→        return timeUp;\n   100→    }\n   101→\n   102→    public void setTimeUp(Instant timeUp) {\n   103→        this.timeUp = timeUp;\n   104→    }\n   105→}\n   106→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"356d438e-1261-40b0-9ccb-c7f88eaae569"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G2oRwcTveME4ZZRvjR9FxA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.kitchen.domain;\n     2→\n     3→import io.agroal.api.AgroalDataSource;\n     4→import io.quarkus.agroal.DataSource;\n     5→import io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheRepository;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→public class KitchenOrderRepository implements PanacheRepository<KitchenOrder> {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    @DataSource(\"kitchen\")\n    15→    AgroalDataSource kitchenDataSource;\n    16→\n    17→}\n    18→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"56a106d4-574a-4952-b50c-6c3ebcbbdf4a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BQ2yyAd1Fb7pbRdBXBLtZQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.utils;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jdk8.Jdk8Module;\n     6→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\n     7→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderIn;\n     8→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderUp;\n     9→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n    10→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n    11→\n    12→public class JsonUtil {\n    13→\n    14→    private static Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(JsonUtil.class);\n    15→\n    16→    private static final ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper()\n    17→            .registerModules(new JavaTimeModule(),new Jdk8Module());\n    18→\n    19→    public static String toJson(final Object object) {\n    20→        LOGGER.debug(\"marshalling {} to JSON\", object.toString());\n    21→        try {\n    22→            return objectMapper.writeValueAsString(object);\n    23→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    24→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    25→            return \"{ \\\"error\\\" : \\\"\" + e.getMessage() + \"\\\" }\";\n    26→        }\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    public static <T> T fromJson(final String json, Class clazz) {\n    30→        try {\n    31→            return (T) objectMapper.readValue(json, clazz);\n    32→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    33→            e.printStackTrace();\n    34→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    35→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    36→        }\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    public static OrderUp fromJsonToOrderUp(String json) {\n    40→        try {\n    41→            return objectMapper.readValue(json, OrderUp.class);\n    42→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    43→            e.printStackTrace();\n    44→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    45→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    46→        }\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public static OrderIn fromJsonToOrderIn(String json) {\n    50→        try {\n    51→            return objectMapper.readValue(json, OrderIn.class);\n    52→        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n    53→            e.printStackTrace();\n    54→            LOGGER.error(e.getMessage());\n    55→            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n    56→        }\n    57→    }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"ca3de31a-e7a5-47b1-bf48-ec759ac41ce3"}
