           <div class=\"box wow fadeInUp\" data-wow-duration=\"1.2s\" data-wow-offset=\"10\">\n   735→                    <img src=\"images/headshots/ken_avatar_2019.png\" alt=\"Ken Finnigan\" />\n   736→                    <h6>Ken Finnigan</h6>\n   737→                    <p>Pre-Quarkus Co-Founder</p>\n   738→                </div>\n   739→            </div>\n   740→            <div class=\"col-md-2\">\n   741→                <div class=\"box wow fadeInUp\" data-wow-duration=\"1.6s\" data-wow-offset=\"10\">\n   742→                    <img src=\"images/headshots/max-andersen.jpg\" alt=\"Max Andersen\" />\n   743→                    <h6>Max Andersen</h6>\n   744→                    <p>Devex Lead</p>\n   745→                </div>\n   746→            </div>\n   747→            <div class=\"col-md-2\">\n   748→                <div class=\"box wow fadeInUp\" data-wow-duration=\"1.6s\" data-wow-offset=\"10\">\n   749→                    <img src=\"images/headshots/clement_escoffier.jpeg\" alt=\"Clement Escoffier\" />\n   750→                    <h6>Clement Escoffier</h6>\n   751→                    <p>Reactive Lead</p>\n   752→                </div>\n   753→            </div>\n   754→        </div>\n   755→    </div>\n   756→</section>\n   757→<span class=\"anchor\" id=\"testimonials\"></span>\n   758→<section class=\"testimonials\">\n   759→    <div id=\"carousel-testimonials\" class=\"carousel slide\" data-bs-ride=\"carousel\">\n   760→        <div class=\"container-fluid padding-2x\">\n   761→            <!-- Wrapper for slides -->\n   762→            <div class=\"row\">\n   763→                <div class=\"col-xs-12\">\n   764→                    <h3 class=\"text-center\">Twitter</h3>\n   765→                    <hr>\n   766→                </div>\n   767→            </div>\n   768→            <div class=\"row\">\n   769→                <div class=\"col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3\">\n   770→                    <div class=\"carousel-inner\">\n   771→                        <div class=\"carousel-item active\">\n   772→                            <div class=\"carousel-content\">\n   773→                                <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet tw-align-center \"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">I really like <a href=\"https://twitter.com/QuarkusIO?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@QuarkusIO</a>&#39;s extension system. The deployment time (build time) hook allows for a lot of interesting uses I haven&#39;t thought of yet 🚀</p>&mdash; Knut Wannheden (@knutwannheden) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/knutwannheden/status/1276588974849634304?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">June 26, 2020</a></blockquote> <script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n   774→                            </div>\n   775→                        </div>\n   776→                        <div class=\"carousel-item\">\n   777→                            <div class=\"carousel-content\">\n   778→                                <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet tw-align-center \"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">“One of the real benefits of <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/Java?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#Java</a> is that it does have a huge <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/ecosystem?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#ecosystem</a> of <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/libraries?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#libraries</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/utilities?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#utilities</a> for doing practically everything.&quot; Therefore, consider using the <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/Quarkus?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#Quarkus</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/framework?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#framework</a> for your next <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/microservice?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#microservice</a> project. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/QuarkusIO?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@QuarkusIO</a><a href=\"https://t.co/Z6JNMFSxab\">https://t.co/Z6JNMFSxab</a></p>&mdash; Felix Seifert (@flx_seifert) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/flx_seifert/status/1274708071630045185?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">June 21, 2020</a></blockquote> <script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n   779→                            </div>\n   780→                        </div>\n   781→                        <div class=\"carousel-item\">\n   782→                            <div class=\"carousel-content\">\n   783→                                <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet tw-align-center \"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">⚡️New: Running a native image on AWS <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/Lambda?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#Lambda</a> through <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/Quarkus?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#Quarkus</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/GraalVM?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#GraalVM</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/sascha242?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@sascha242</a> and me examine the benefits you can get and describe the build steps required for your <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/Java?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#Java</a> app. <a href=\"https://t.co/yRSSEvOSuz\">https://t.co/yRSSEvOSuz</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/6H7OOi3geF\">pic.twitter.com/6H7OOi3geF</a></p>&mdash; Steffen Grunwald (@steffeng) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/steffeng/status/1273485530030903298?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">June 18, 2020</a></blockquote> <script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n   784→                            </div>\n   785→                        </div>\n   786→                        <!-- Indicators -->\n   787→                        <div class=\"carousel-indicators\">\n   788→                            <button type=\"button\" data-bs-target=\"#carousel-testimonials\" data-bs-slide-to=\"0\" class=\"active\" aria-current=\"true\" aria-label=\"Slide 1\"></button>\n   789→  