Or let us know what you thought about the demo?</p>\n   885→            </div>\n   886→        </div>\n   887→        <div class=\"row\">\n   888→            <div class=\"col-xs-12 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2\">\n   889→                <form>\n   890→                    <div class=\"form-group col-md-6\">\n   891→                        <input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Name\" class=\"form-control\" id=\"name\">\n   892→                    </div>\n   893→                    <div class=\"form-group col-md-6\">\n   894→                        <input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Email\" class=\"form-control\" id=\"email\">\n   895→                    </div>\n   896→                    <div class=\"form-group col-xs-12\">\n   897→                        <input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Subject\" class=\"form-control\" id=\"subject\">\n   898→                    </div>\n   899→                    <div class=\"form-group col-xs-12\">\n   900→                        <textarea class=\"form-control\" placeholder=\"How can we help you?\" rows=\"6\" id=\"message\"></textarea>\n   901→                    </div>\n   902→                    <button type=\"submit\" class=\"btn btn-default\">Submit</button>\n   903→                </form>\n   904→            </div>\n   905→        </div>\n   906→        <div class=\"row contact-boxes\">\n   907→            <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\n   908→                <div class=\"box wow fadeInUp\" data-wow-duration=\"400ms\" data-wow-offset=\"10\">\n   909→                    <i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>\n   910→                    <h6>Visit With Us</h6>\n   911→                    <p><a href=\"https://quarkus.io\">Quarkus.io</a></p>\n   912→                </div>\n   913→            </div>\n   914→            <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\n   915→                <div class=\"box wow fadeInUp\" data-wow-duration=\"800ms\" data-wow-offset=\"10\">\n   916→                    <i class=\"fa fa-phone\"></i>\n   917→                    <h6>Get In Touch</h6>\n   918→                    <p><a href=\"https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com\" >Quarkus Zulip Chat</a></p>\n   919→                    <p><a href=\"https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/quarkus-dev\">Google Groups</a></p>\n   920→                </div>\n   921→            </div>\n   922→            <div class=\"col-lg-4\">\n   923→                <div class=\"box wow fadeInUp\" data-wow-duration=\"1.2s\" data-wow-offset=\"10\">\n   924→                    <i class=\"fa fa-clock-o\"></i>\n   925→                    <h6>Hours of Operation</h6>\n   926→                    <p>Monday-Friday: 9am-7pm<br />\n   927→                        Saturday &amp; Sunday: 8am-8pm\n   928→                    </p>\n   929→                </div>\n   930→            </div>\n   931→        </div>\n   932→    </div>\n   933→</section>\n   934→<section class=\"footer\">\n   935→    <div class=\"container\">\n   936→        <div class=\"row\">\n   937→            <div class=\"col-xs-12\">\n   938→                <ul class=\"list-inline text-center margin-bottom\">\n   939→                    <li><a href=\"\"><i class=\"fa fa-facebook\"></i></a></li>\n   940→                    <li><a href=\"\"><i class=\"fa fa-twitter\"></i></a></li>\n   941→                    <li><a href=\"\"><i class=\"fa fa-linkedin\"></i></a></li>\n   942→                    <li><a href=\"\"><i class=\"fa fa-behance\"></i></a></li>\n   943→                </ul>\n   944→                <p class=\"text-center\">© 2018 <a href=\"http://hh-themes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">HH Themes</a></p>\n   945→                <!-- Please do not remove the backlink to us unless you have purchased a license. It is part of the license conditions. Thanks for understanding :) -->\n   946→            </div>\n   947→        </div>\n   948→    </div>\n   949→    <div id=\"back-to-top\"><i class=\"fa fa-arrow-circle-up\"></i></div>\n   950→</section>\n   951→<div class=\".d-none\"></div>\n   952→<appvalues id=\"appvalues\"\n   953→           data-store-id=\"{storeId}\"\n   954→           data-stream-url=\"{streamUrl}\"\n   955→/>\n   956→<!-- jQuery (necessary for Bootstrap's JavaScript plugins) -->\n   957→<script src=\"https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.7.1/jquery.min.js\"></script>\n   958→<!-- Include all compiled plugins (below), or include individual files as needed -->\n   959→<script src=\"js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\"></script>\n   960→<script src=\"js/jquery.matchHeight.js\"></script>\n   961→<script src=\"js/jquery.cookie.js\"></script>\n   962→<script src=\"js/custom.js\"></script>\n   963→<script src=\"js/cafe.js\"></script>\n   964→<script src=\"js/wow.js\"></script>\n   965→<script src=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/ekko-lightbox/5.3.0/ekko-lightbox.js\"></script>\n   966→<script src=\"js/toastr.js\"></script>\n   967→<script>\n   968→    new WOW().init();\n   969→</script>\n   970→<script>\n   971→    $(document).on('click', '[data-toggle=\"lightbox\"]', function(event) {\n   972→        event.preventDefault();\n   973→        $(this).ekkoLightbox();\n   974→    });\n   975→</script>\n   976→\n   977→\n   978→</body>\n   979→</html>\n   980→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"f22c3be0-d79f-41c3-a1a7-a8b32290c929"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_018Bmz1yvcKLPc15vm59b4tD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me update my task list and begin the migration. The key Quarkus-specific features that need migration:\n\n1. **Panache ORM** (PanacheEntity, PanacheEntityBase, PanacheRepository)  \n2. **Quarkus Vert.x EventBus** (@ConsumeEvent, EventBus)\n3. **SmallRye Reactive Messaging** (@Incoming, @Channel, Emitter)\n4. **Quarkus Qute templating** (Template, TemplateInstance)\n5. **Quarkus @Startup** annotation\n6. **Quarkus @DataSource** qualifier\n7. **Agroal DataSource**\n8. **MicroProfile Config** (@ConfigProperty)\n9. **SmallRye Mutiny** (Multi, Uni)\n\nThe target is a standalone Jakarta EE application. I'll use an embedded approach with Open Liberty or a lightweight WAR-based approach. Given the complexity, the most practical approach is to use a lightweight runtime. Let me go with **Open Liberty** (Jakarta EE 10) which supports all needed features, or better yet, use **WildFly** with bootable JAR. \n\nActually, the most pragmatic approach for \"Jakarta\" is to create a standalone application using Jakarta EE APIs with an embedded server. Let me use **WildFly Bootable JAR** or **Payara Micro** or **Open Liberty**. Given the constraints, I'll use **Open Liberty** with Jakarta EE 10.\n\nLet me rethink - the simplest and most robust approach: migrate to a plain **Jakarta EE** application running on **WildFly** (or Open Liberty). I'll restructure to use standard Jakarta EE APIs:\n- JAX-RS for REST\n- JPA (Hibernate) instead of Panache  \n- CDI events instead of Vert.x EventBus\n- Standard datasource config\n- Drop Kafka/reactive messaging (simplify to in-process)\n- Replace Qute with simple HTML serving"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2081,"cache_creation_input_tokens":18499,"cache_read_input_tokens":70491,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":18499,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":986},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"887ed637-45f4-4598-acb3-9e086d9e5f12","uuid":"4b2ed27b-ef9a-41c7-a9cc-d206a9567873"}
